Van Dijk: &ldquo;Kane is a fantastic striker, one of the best in England, and definitely the best striker England have got for the national team.<br />
<br />
Van Dijk: &ldquo;But I know also that, if you're not 100 per cent fit, it'll be in your head if you get a bit of a knock or you get a bit of pain when you pass it. I expected him to play the final, but not at 100 per cent. I don't know if he'll play tomorrow, but we'll see.&rdquo;

Lallana: &quot;I know my ability and I know what I can give. And the gaffer and his staff and the recruitment guys have all made it clear they know I have a big part to play with what's to come next, so I'm buzzing with that.&quot;<br />
<br />
Lallana: <span style="color: red;">&quot;It means so much to my best mate (Jordan Henderson) for different reasons</span>. I am just so happy to be out there among it with the team and feel that cohesion. That's what's brought us here.&quot;
